<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
I was sitting in the ideas forum today, when Massimiliano Marangio broached the idea of a module set in the world of Glorantha. Now as a player of various P&amp;P RPGs in that world, I thought "hey, cool!", and posted an bulletin announcing that I am prepared to make such a module. (It was also a non-so-subtle request for help). <p>
<a href=".forum.t-o-m-e.net/viewtopic.php?t=5058&amp;sid=c70450786629fccdc17ac3e75674406c">http://forum.t-o-m-e.net/viewtopic.php?t=5058&amp;sid=c70450786629fccdc17ac3e75674406c</a> 
</p>
<p>
<a class="external" href=".www.glorantha.com/"><img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/moin-www.png" alt="[WWW]" height="11" width="11">http://www.Glorantha.com</a> 
</p>
<p>
Let me know if you have any thoughts on the matter! 
</p>
<p>
Blackdog 
</p>
<hr>
 <p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: As I said in the forum, I will try to help with the module. 
</p>
